                <head>Abandoned</head>
                <origin/>
                <commentary/>
                <trailer/>
                <names/>
                <summary>A several-month-old child was found abandoned on a lot on the Franklin
                    Railroad near T. B. Wood and Co.'s foundry. The mother was found shortly
                    therefter. "She had been a servant at the Montgomery Hotel, and gave birth to
                    the child at the County Poor House. The mother is a yellow woman, and after it
                    was ascertained to whom the child belonged, she took the child and placed it
                    with a colored family in town."</summary>
